The official PitchBook Model Context Protocol (MCP) server provides AI agents with standardized, secure access to private market data, including company details, financial data, deals, and investor information [1][2]. It is maintained by PitchBook and requires an active PitchBook license for Premium access [1][3].

To configure the server in an MCP-compatible client like Claude Desktop or Cursor, add the following to your configuration file [1]:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "pitchbook": {
      "url": "https://premium.mcp.pitchbook.com/mcp"
    }
  }
}
```

The server enables tools such as get_company, get_financials, search_companies, search_deals, and search_investors [1]. Usage is primarily intended for private equity, venture capital, and investment banking workflows [3]. While the Premium version requires a direct license, PitchBook also offers an Essential MCP connector with limited data access [3].
